FBIS4-60489 "drnes101_j_94001" FBIS-NES-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Salih Receives Cable From al-Bid's `Private Guard' Salih Receives Cable From al-Bid's `Private Guard' JN2405174094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1700 GMT 24 May 94 JN2405174094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council and supreme commander of the Armed Forces, has received a cable from the officers, NCO's, and soldiers of the (?al-Khurafi) camp, who used to be called the private guard of traitor 'Ali Salim al-Bid. The cable voices the congratulations of the officers, noncommissioned officers [NCO's], and soldiers to the brother leader president and supreme commander of the Armed Forces on the occasion of the blessed 'Id al-Adha and the fourth national anniversary of the Republic of Yemen and also expresses support for the forces of unity and legitimacy. The cable condemns what was done by the gang of apostasy and secession in the Yemeni Socialist Party, led by traitor 'Ali Salim al-Bid, namely, the declaration of secession, stressing that it is considered high treason against the homeland, the unity, and the Yemeni people and that history will not forgive that gang's crimes against the people and the homeland. The officers, NCO's, and soldiers in the al-Khurafi camp expressed their great appreciation for the step the leadership has taken under brother LIt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih to preserve the homeland's unity and safeguard its gains, which were achieved for our people under the immortal Yemeni revolution. They also stressed their determination to defend unity under the Republic of Yemen.
